      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Method",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Day 1: dough and lamination",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Follow the croissant dough method: mix the {{strong-bread-flour}}, {{caster-sugar}}, {{sea-salt-fine}}, {{yeast-fast-action}}, cold {{whole-milk}} and first {{unsalted-butter}} in a stand mixer for 6 minutes. Shape, wrap, chill 1 hour. Beat the second {{unsalted-butter}} into a 20×15 cm rectangle and chill. Lock the butter into the dough; do three single folds with 30-minute rests between each. Chill overnight.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Day 2: roll with cinnamon sugar, shape",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Mix the {{soft-brown-sugar}} with the first 18 g of {{cinnamon-ground}}. Roll the laminated dough to a 45×30 cm rectangle, 4 mm thick. Brush lightly with water. Scatter the cinnamon sugar evenly over. From a long edge, roll up tightly into a sausage. Slice into 12 spirals. Press each cut-side-up into a well-greased muffin tin hole. Proof at room temperature for 2 hours until puffed and the spirals are pressing against the sides of the tin.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Bake, toss in cinnamon sugar",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Heat the oven to 190°C fan. Bake for 25 to 30 minutes; the buns should be deep gold all over and the cinnamon-sugar layers should be visible. Mix the second {{caster-sugar}} with the second {{cinnamon-ground}} in a shallow bowl. While the buns are still hot, lift each from the tin and toss in the cinnamon-sugar to coat. Cool on a rack.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
  },
